quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  21,58,"So he broke them to pieces, (all) except the biggest of them, that they might turn to it.",""
  21,59,"They said: ""Who has done this to our âlihah (gods)? He must indeed be one of the Zâlimun (wrong-doers).""",""
  21,60,"They said: ""We heard a young man talking against them, who is called Ibrâhîm (Abraham).""",""
  21,61,"They said: ""Then bring him before the eyes of the people, that they may testify.""",""
  21,62,"They said: ""Are you the one who has done this to our gods, O Ibrâhîm (Abraham)?""",""
  21,63,"[Ibrâhîm (Abraham)] said: ""Nay, this one, the biggest of them (idols) did it. Ask them, if they can speak!""<sup>5</sup>","[5] (V.21:63) See the footnote (C) of (V.16:121)."
  21,64,"So they turned to themselves and said: ""Verily, you are the Zâlimûn (polytheists and wrong-doers).""",""
  21,65,"Then they turned to themselves (their first thought and said): ""Indeed you [Ibrâhîm (Abraham)] know well that these (idols) speak not!""",""
  21,66,"[Ibrâhîm (Abraham)] said: ""Do you then worship besides Allâh, things that can neither profit you, nor harm you?",""
  21,67,"""Fie upon you, and upon that which you worship besides Allâh! Have you then no sense?""",""
  21,68,"They said: ""Burn him and help your âlihah (gods), if you will be doing.""",""
  21,69,"We (Allâh) said: ""O fire! Be you coolness and safety for Ibrâhîm (Abraham)!""",""
  21,70,"And they wanted to harm him, but We made them the worst losers.",""
  21,71,"And We rescued him and Lût (Lot) to the land which We have blessed for the ‘Âlamîn (mankind and jinn).",""
  21,72,"And We bestowed upon him Ishâq (Isaac), and (a grandson) Ya‘qûb (Jacob). Each one We made righteous.",""
